GateDocument.TextWithNodes: Call for Papers CIKM'98 Workshop on Web Information and Data Management ( WIDM'98 ) Washington DC , USA , November 6 , 1998 In conjunction with ACM CIKM'98 : Seventh International Conference on Information and Knowledge Management Sponsored by ACM SIGIR and SIGMIS OBJECTIVES : Providing effective and efficient access to the vast information available on the web has become a critical research area in recent years . Further , large amounts of data reside in non-database applications such as desktop applications ( spreadsheet , wordprocessors , etc . . . ) , E- mail messages , bibliography files ( such as BibTex ) , and , more generally , semi-structured and unstructured repositories . This workshop is intended to bring together researchers in the database and information retrieval areas to assess current methodologies and explore new approaches to the problems of the management and retrieval of information on the web and non-database repositories ; and the interoperability of databases and non-database information sources . The following is a non-exclusive list of topics of interest : - Modeling of web and non-database repositories . - Query languages for the web . - Query processing and optimization . - Indexing techniques for web and non-database repositories . - Data caching on the web . - Resource discovery . - Discovering structure in web and non-database repositories . - Information integration . SUBMISSION : Submissions should be approximately 10 pages ( double spaced ) in length . Papers will be reviewed by the program committee for their technical merit , originality , significance , and relevance to the workshop . We strongly encourage email submissions . The title page must include the name and email address of the contact author . To submit , you can either send your paper in PostScript form to the email address below ( this is the preferred option ) , or send 4 hardcopies of your paper to the following address , no later than August 28 , 1998 .
